data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Resin (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Kids ‘Resin’ makes use of a lightweight polyester upper, secured with elastic no-tie laces and finished in a yellowish green hue. Contrasting black no-sew overlays at the forefoot and heel are enlivened with reflective detailing, good for enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. Branding is limited to a metallic silver 700 logo on the lateral side. The sneaker sits atop a sculpted black polyurethane midsole, which houses full-length drop-in Boost cushioning for a smooth ride.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre (Infants)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Infants ‘Ochre’ delivers a neutral colorway of a street-ready sandal made for little feet. Rendered in an uneven finish, a light brown hue floods the minimalist build, crafted from rubberized foam with textured surfaces. The footbed offers step-in comfort, highlighted by a soft top layer marked with adidas’ three-stripe branding. Underfoot, the outsole features aggressive horizontal grooves that yield enhanced cushioning and traction.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Kids ‘Ochre’ applies an uneven light brown finish to the fashion-forward sandal, featuring a rubberized foam build with a textured surface. The minimalist design is free of any exterior branding, save for adidas’ three-stripe logo stamped on the soft top layer of the footbed. Open-toe construction delivers ventilated comfort, while an aggressive sawtooth-pattern outsole provides a blend of cushioning and traction for a smooth ride.

adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Light’ introduces UV-sensitive technology to the Yeezy franchise. When exposed to direct sunlight, the flexible Primeknit upper transitions from off-white to a subtle pink hue, while the post-dyed monofilament side stripe takes on a darker shade of amber. The sock-like build is secured with traditional lace closure and equipped with a webbing pull tab at the heel for easy on and off. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a wrapped Boost midsole, fully visible through cut-outs in the rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas NMD R1 Black Pulse Yellow (PS)
adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bright Cyan (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Kids ‘Bright Cyan’ pairs a minimalist build with ultra-responsive cushioning. No-tie bungee laces secure a seamless upper crafted from a single piece of lightweight polyester in a vibrant blue finish. Emblazoned across the lateral side panel is silver reflective ‘700’ branding in a reverse mirror print. The sneaker is mounted on a sculpted black polyurethane midsole, enhanced with full-length drop-in Boost cushioning within and a herringbone-tread rubber outsole underfoot.

data.name: adidas Stan Smith Toy Story Rex the Dinosaur (PS)
adidas Stan Smith Marvel Hulk Smash (PS)
adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Ash Pearl’ shows off split color blocking on a sock-like upper constructed from breathable Primeknit. The top-down view reveals a visible seam that runs down the vamp, separating varying tan and grey shades on the lateral and medial sides. The former is accented with a monofilament side stripe, which gives way to more grey tones on the lower portion of the shoe. Decorated with no-tie elastic laces, the upper is mounted atop full-length Boost midsole.

data.name: adidas Sport Shoe LEGO Shock Blue Multi-Color (PS)
adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red (Kids)
data.story: Launching in December 2020, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Bred’ brings back a simplistic two-tone colorway of the lifestyle silhouette first released in 2017. The reissue is unchanged from the original, featuring a black Primeknit upper with ‘SPLY-350’ inscribed in reverse-print red lettering on the lateral side panel. An additional pop of red appears via embroidered detailing on a pull tab at the heel. The sneaker rides on a full-length Boost midsole, entirely wrapped in a semi-translucent rubber cage.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Onyx Non-Reflective’ offers a subdued colorway of the minimalist silhouette, featuring a composition of black and dark brown fibers that make up the re-engineered Primeknit upper. The resulting camo-like design is interrupted on the sneaker’s lateral side, where a post dyed monofilament side stripe sweeps through the midfoot. A smokey rubber cage envelops the Boost midsole, visible through cut-outs in the gum rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Kids ‘Safflower’ presents a subtle colorway of the sleek silhouette, highlighted by flowing yellow lines throughout the monofilament engineered mesh upper. The lightweight build is reinforced with a glow-in-the-dark RPU cage for added support and durability, while a contrasting black interior bootie provides a snug, one-to-one fit. An ivory hue coats the PU encapsulated EVA midsole, supported underfoot by a herringbone rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Teal Blue (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum Kids ‘Teal Blue’ makes use of a Primeknit upper in a subtle palette of grey, black and teal. Silver reflective thread is woven into the side panels, forming wavy lines that provide added visibility in low-light conditions. A two-tone heel cap is similarly rendered in reflective finish, while matte black neoprene is utilized on the collar and tongue. The minimalist build rides on a full-length Boost midsole, encased in semi-translucent rubber for improved stability.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Carbon’ delivers a neutral colorway of the slip-on sneaker, secured with no-tie bungee laces for a snug fit. The upper makes use of breathable Primeknit in a mostly black finish with varying shades of grey throughout. On the lateral side, a black monofilament side stripe cuts through the two-tone woven paneling. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length Boost midsole, encased entirely in semi-translucent rubber.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Pepper Non-Reflective’ features subtle hues on a minimalist silhouette that does away with rigid structure and clearly defined lines. Instead, the sock-like Primeknit build highlights an amorphous, camo-like pattern, made up of beige and light grey hues that are contrasted by a splash of orange on the post-dyed monofilament side stripe. A full-length Boost midsole, confined within a greyish blue rubber cage, delivers a cushioned ride.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Israfil’ features a breathable Primeknit upper that combines a blend of yarns in pale yellow and bluish-grey hues, rendered in different woven patterns for a patchwork-like effect. A post-dyed monofilament side stripe in orange delivers a pop of color on the sneaker’s lateral side. Secured with elastic no-tie laces, the minimalist silhouette rides on a full-length Boost midsole, reinforced with a semi-translucent rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Blue Oat Non-Reflective’ showcases clashing hues throughout the breathable Primeknit upper. A streak of royal blue stands out on the translucent monofilament window woven into the side panel, contrasted by a blend of orange and brown hues arranged in a camo-like pattern. The lightweight build is supported by a Boost midsole, encased in semi-translucent rubber and supported by a herringbone rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Zyon’ delivers a neutral colorway of Kanye West’s lifestyle sneaker, highlighted by complementary grey and brown tones on a stretchy Primeknit upper. Traditional lace closure enhances the fit of the slip-on silhouette, while a black monofilament side stripe provides added breathability. The lightweight build rests on a full-length Boost midsole, visible through cut-out detailing on the rubber midsole.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Kids ‘Bone’ features a tan polyester upper, accented on the lateral side panel with oversized 700 branding in a reflective silver finish. The lightweight build is secured with no-tie bungee laces, while contrasting black overlays provide added durability. A matching black PU midsole houses full-length drop-in Boost cushioning, visible underfoot through cut-out detailing on the herringbone rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Barium (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum Kids ‘Barium’ makes use of a grey jacquard knit inlay reinforced with a translucent RPU cage on the side panels. A synthetic suede toe cap delivers added durability, while reflective detailing throughout the upper provides enhanced visibility in low-light conditions, including the seamless external heel counter. The midsole features a full-length Boost unit in a semi-translucent TPU cage.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Black (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Kids ‘Triple Black’ delivers a monochromatic take on Kanye West’s maximalist lifestyle runner. The upper, built with lightweight polyester and synthetic no-sew overlays, features reflective detailing throughout, including the oversized 700 branding that adorns the sneaker’s side panels. No-tie bungee laces provide a snug fit, while a full-length drop-in Boost midsole is good for a responsive ride.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Kids ‘Phosphor’ applies a neon yellow finish to a one-piece polyester upper, secured with no-tie bungee laces and fortified with contrasting black-no sew overlays. The two-tone color scheme is accented by reflective silver detailing, highlighted by oversized 700 branding on the lateral side panel. A sculpted PU midsole packs a full-length drop-in Boost unit for lightweight and responsive cushioning.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Earth Brown (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Slides Kids ‘Earth Brown’ features a subdued monochromatic finish on Kanye West’s minimalist sandal. Built with lightweight EVA, the unibody build makes use of a single-strap setup with a soft top layer on the footbed, good for immediate step-in comfort and marked with adidas’ three-stripe branding. The slip-on rides atop an outsole equipped with exaggerated flex grooves that deliver enhanced traction with each step.

data.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Kids ‘Alvah’ features a subdued color scheme, highlighted by a black monofilament mesh upper with flowing grey stripes. An exoskeletal overlay in glow-in-the-dark RPU provides structure to the sneaker’s side panels, while a rubberized toe cap is good for lightweight durability. Reflective detailing offers added visibility at the base of the tongue. In lieu of Boost cushioning, the sneaker uses a bulky EVA midsole.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Mist (Kids)
data.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Mist Non-Reflective’ features a breathable Primeknit upper finished in varying grey shades that form an all-over camo-like pattern. An elastic collar delivers a snug fit, while perforated detailing increases ventilation on the side panel, which is further highlighted by a semi-translucent patch of tan coloring. The tooling consists of a responsive Boost midsole, reinforced with a durable gum rubber outsole for grippy traction.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Desert Sage’ features a subtle green hue on the lightweight Primeknit upper, accented with a reflective monofilament side stripe and a contrasting pop of orange on the collar. A brighter shade of green is applied to the semi-translucent rubber cage that surrounds the full-length Boost midsole, exposed underfoot through cut-out detailing on the pale orange rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange (Kids)
data.story: The Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Kids ‘Orange’ updates the retro-inspired silhouette with an eye-catching finish on the lightweight polyester upper. Reflective accents are littered throughout the minimalist design, including oversized ‘700’ branding emblazoned across the lateral side panel. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length drop-in Boost midsole, visible through cut-outs in the herringbone rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Yeshaya’ delivers a neutral take on the minimalist lifestyle silhouette, featuring a mix of different woven patterns throughout the breathable Primeknit upper. The grey and white patchwork-like design is mounted atop a full-length Boost midsole, encased in a semi-translucent rubber cage in an Off-White finish. A grippy gum rubber outsole provides durable traction underfoot.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant ‘Yecheil’ utilizes sharply contrasting hues throughout the sneaker’s re-engineered Primeknit upper, accented with a black monofilament stripe that bisects the side panel. Reflective thread is woven into the rope laces, adding a high-vis element to the miniaturized build. Responsive cushioning arrives via the sneaker’s full-length Boost midsole, visible through cut-out detailing in the black rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Tensaur Run Core Black (Kids)
data.story: Made for little kids, the adidas Tensaur Run C ‘Core Black’ features a breathable black mesh upper with dual midfoot straps that replace traditional lace closure. Synthetic leather overlays offer added durability at the toe and heel, the latter equipped with a pull tab for easy on and off. Contrasting white three-stripes are matched by lightweight EVA midsole, supported by a waffle traction pattern underfoot for optimal grip.

data.name: adidas Tensaur Run Shock Pink (Kids)
data.story: Made for little kids, the adidas Tensaur Run C ‘Shock Pink’ highlights an eye-catching hue on the upper, constructed from breathable mesh with tonal synthetic leather overlays at the toe and heel. Contrasting white hits appear on the floating three-stripes and pull tab, good for easy one and off. The versatile runner is mounted atop a white EVA midsole for lightweight cushioning. Up top, dual midfoot straps offer a custom fit.

data.name: adidas Tensaur Run Team Royal (Kids)
data.story: Made for little kids, the adidas Tensaur Run C ‘Team Royal’ features a breathable mesh upper with synthetic leather overlays at the toe and heel. Dual adjustable midfoot straps replace a traditional lacing system, offering easy entry and a custom fit. Prominent stitch detailing on the side panel delivers added style, while floating white three-stripes complement a matching EVA midsole. A waffle pattern on the outsole is good for enhanced traction.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Bone (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Kids ‘Bone’ applies a monochromatic Off-White finish to the minimalist slip-on sandal, constructed from molded EVA foam for lightweight comfort. Exterior branding is limited to adidas’ three-stripe logo, debossed at the base of the contoured footbed. A series of deep horizontal grooves are built into the outsole, good for enhanced traction and flexibility with each step.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Desert Sand (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Kids ‘Desert Sand’ combines plush comfort with a futuristic, minimalist design, executed on a lightweight EVA build and finished in a refined hue. The unibody upper is stripped of any exterior branding, save for adidas’ three-stripe logo debossed on the cushioned footbed. An aggressive traction pattern distinguishes the outsole, delivering optimal grip and impact absorption underfoot.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Resin (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Kids ‘Resin’ showcases a subtle monochromatic finish on a minimalist sandal constructed from lightweight EVA foam. Exterior branding is limited to adidas’ three-stripe logo, debossed on the plush top layer of the footbed. A series of strategically placed flex grooves are utilized on the outsole, providing a combination of grippy traction and impact absorption with each step.

data.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Stone (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Kids ‘Stone’ updates the chunky retro-inspired silhouette with a subdued monochromatic finish. The sneaker’s layered construction utilizes a blend of stretchy Lycra, soft cow suede and premium leather. Reflective piping offers added visibility in low-light conditions, while an abrasion-resistant rubber overlays wraps around the base of the upper, giving way to a podular midsole built with adiPRENE+ cushioning.

data.name: adidas D.O.N. Issue #1 Mailman Karl Malone (PS)
adidas Yeezy 500 Soft Vision (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Kids symbolizes Kanye West's directional design intent with a throwback influence. Updated in November 2019, this version has a mesh, cow suede and premium leather upper expressed in a monochromatic Soft Vision scheme. Reflective piping surrounds the lace eyelets and a protective mudguard wraps the sidewall. The sneaker tools a tonal midsole with Adiprene+ cushioning and a gum rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Harden Vol. 4 Star Wars (PS)
data.story: Launching as part of a larger collection celebrating the iconic sci-fi film franchise, the Star Wars x adidas Harden Vol. 4 Little Kids ‘Lightsaber’ draws inspiration from Mace Windu’s weapon of choice, featuring purple accents throughout the knit upper. A matching violet hue is applied to the springy Bounce midsole, finished in a glowing UV coating meant to replicate the look of a lightsaber. Reflective laces are secured with metallic gold eyestays and accented with Star Wars-branded dubrae.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Kids)
data.story: First introduced as part of the Season 3 collection, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids returns Kanye West's iconic design with pared-down styling. This Citrin version—revealed in September 2019—serves up a non-reflective Primeknit bootie teamed with integrated lacing and the signature translucent monofilament stripe across the lateral. A two-tone Tubular rubber outsole, assisted by responsive Boost technology, is placed below.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White (Kids)
adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Kids pulls iconic technology from the German brand's archives, packaging them into a retro-influenced sneaker driven by Kanye West's design ethos. Arrived in August 2019, this edition is crafted of Bone White mesh, cow suede and leather. Reinforced laces and reflective piping around the eyelets hint at a utilitarian aesthetic. An AdiPRENE+ midsole and rubber outsole supply cushioning and grip.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner Solid Grey (Kids)
data.story: Reissued in August 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Kids 'Wave Runner' was first revealed at the Season 5 runway show. This version stays true to the adult original in multicolored mesh counterbalanced by contrasting suede and leather panels. Unique touches include neon-colored laces and perforation on heel. A Boost-cushioned midsole and herringbone rubber outsole give the sneaker its distinctively retro look.

data.name: adidas Ozweego Core Black Solar Green (PS)
adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Lundmark Non-Reflective' sneaker brings together form and function, melding future-forward design and athletic performance. Unveiled in July 2019, this update presents a translucent monofilament stripe traversing the lateral of a duo-tone Primeknit upper. Patterned rope laces are integrated into the bootie. Underfoot, a semi-transparent tubular Boost-assisted sole provides energized cushioning.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Synth (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Synth' sneaker is characterized by minimalist design principles and progressive cues as envisioned by Kanye West. Regionally launched in June 2019, this edition's duo-tone Primeknit upper features patterned rope laces and a transparent stripe on the lateral side. Three-Stripes detailing is seen at the interior heel. A Boost-encapsulated tubular sole optimizes impact support.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 2019 Toy Story 4 Woody (Kids)
data.story: The Three-Stripes brand and Disney teamed up to drop remixed kids’ versions of some of adidas’ most popular models to celebrate the fourth installment of the beloved Toy Story franchise. Released in June 2019, the Toy Story 4 x UltraBoost 19 C 'Woody' sneaker consists of a Woody-inspired colorway, constructed with a Primeknit upper and a structured lacing cage. Boost cushioning and a Woody sockliner deliver energizing comfort.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 2019 Toy Story Buzz Lightyear (Kids)
data.story: The worlds of sportswear and film collided when adidas partnered up with frequent collaborator, Disney, for a kids’ collection inspired by Toy Story 4, the fourth film in the series. Released in June 2019, the UltraBoost 19 C 'Buzz Lightyear' sneaker features a stretchy Primeknit upper covered in a color scheme inspired by the galactic ranger. The shoe is reinforced with supportive overlays and cushioned with a Buzz Lightyear sockliner.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta (Kids)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Kids 'Vanta' was released in June 2019, bringing an all-black look to the silhouette. This take arrives in youth sizing but retains the stand-out features of the adult style, with a multi-layered mesh upper and suede overlays. The sneaker houses responsive, full-length Boost cushioning within its distinctive chunky sole, a component which debuted on the 700 V1 at the Yeezy Season 5 show in 2017.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (Kids)
data.story: When the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Clay' debuted in late March, 2019, it marked the first time a 350 would be released in adult, kids and infant sizes. The kids'-sized Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Clay' maintains the same features as the adult version. The Primeknit upper comes in an orange-brown hue, with contrast patterns and a horizontal stripe. The bright orange heel tab adds a bit of pop, while the translucent midsole and rubber outsole finish out the look.
